results.name: Number of prime divisors of n-th term of Sylvester's sequence A000058.
comment: All numbers less than 2.5*10^15 in Sylvester's sequence are squarefree and no squareful numbers in this sequence are known (Vardi 1991).
a(n) is currently unknown for all n > 10. - _Jens Kruse Andersen_, Jun 19 2014
reference: Vardi, I. "Are All Euclid Numbers Squarefree?" and "PowerMod to the Rescue." Sections 5.1 and 5.2 in Computational Recreations in Mathematica. Reading, MA: Addison-Wesley, pp. 82-89, 1991.
link: Jens Kruse Andersen, Factorization of Sylvester's sequence
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Sylvester's sequence
